Whether or not you need sprite batching depends on the complexity and performance requirements of your game engine. Immediate mode rendering (rendering things as soon as the caller asks for them) is simple and straightforward but might not be the most efficient way if your game needs to draw a large number of sprites. Batching becomes important when performance starts to be a concern due to the high number of draw calls.

2) **Modifying Rendering Functions:**

